{"wiki_catalogs":[{"id":"a27ae80c-cee6-44e4-8468-57e1ef2e69c9","repo_id":"c0c05551-5d15-47c1-b61f-b8c571f956c1","name":"Project Overview","description":"project-overview","prompt":"Create comprehensive content for the CFCPN Procurement Notice Scraper project overview. Explain its purpose as a Node.js CLI tool for automatically scraping procurement notices from China's Government Procurement Network (金采网/CFCPN). Document the core functionality including automated data collection, structured output in JSON and CSV formats, and command-line interface for controlling scrape scope. Describe the technical architecture using Node.js built-in modules with zero external dependencies. Include both conceptual overviews for beginners explaining what procurement notice scraping is and technical details for experienced developers about the HTTP request handling and data transformation pipeline. Use terminology consistent with the codebase such as 'fetchPage', 'csvEscape', and 'main' functions. Provide practical examples demonstrating common use cases like quick testing with default parameters and bulk data extraction.","progress_status":"completed","dependent_files":"scrape_cfcpn.js","gmt_create":"2026-07-03T17:40:09.1414454+08:00","gmt_modified":"2026-07-03T17:40:43.6188862+08:00","raw_data":"WikiEncrypted:"},{"id":"fbc6d1ac-f536-43a6-8d14-e7de80cca9e1","repo_id":"c0c05551-5d15-47c1-b61f-b8c571f956c1","name":"Getting Started","description":"getting-started","prompt":"Create comprehensive getting started documentation for the CFCPN scraper. Include Node.js environment requirements (version compatibility), installation instructions (no npm packages needed - just download the script), and basic usage examples. Document all three command-line modes: default execution (node scrape_cfcpn.js) for 50 records, page-specific execution (node scrape_cfcpn.js 20) for custom page counts, and full data extraction (node scrape_cfcpn.js all) for complete dataset. Explain expected output files (cfcpn_data.json and cfcpn_data.csv) and their locations. Include troubleshooting tips for common issues like network connectivity problems, API rate limiting, and file permission errors. Provide step-by-step verification that the scraper is working correctly by checking the generated output files.","order":1,"progress_status":"completed","dependent_files":"scrape_cfcpn.js","gmt_create":"2026-07-03T17:40:09.1419706+08:00","gmt_modified":"2026-07-03T17:40:42.4661989+08:00","raw_data":"WikiEncrypted:"},{"id":"747e2229-6e28-43d1-b74f-49cc511cad9a","repo_id":"c0c05551-5d15-47c1-b61f-b8c571f956c1","name":"Core Features","description":"core-features","prompt":"Develop detailed content for the core features of the CFCPN scraper. Thoroughly explain the intelligent pagination system that automatically detects total record count and calculates required pages. Document the progress feedback mechanism showing real-time scraping status and completion percentage. Detail the dual-format output system generating both JSON and CSV files simultaneously. Explain the anti-ban mechanism with 500ms request intervals to avoid being blocked by the target website. Include concrete examples from the actual codebase showing how fetchPage handles HTTP POST requests, how the main function orchestrates the scraping workflow, and how csvEscape ensures proper CSV formatting. Document configuration options like PAGE_SIZE constant and API_URL endpoint. Address error handling strategies and retry mechanisms. Make content accessible to beginners while providing sufficient technical depth for experienced developers who want to understand the implementation details.","order":2,"progress_status":"completed","dependent_files":"scrape_cfcpn.js","gmt_create":"2026-07-03T17:40:09.1419706+08:00","gmt_modified":"2026-07-03T17:40:58.5069219+08:00","raw_data":"WikiEncrypted:"},{"id":"4a460a2c-a6ae-40a0-9c52-ab826946bc32","repo_id":"c0c05551-5d15-47c1-b61f-b8c571f956c1","name":"Data Formats","description":"data-formats","prompt":"Create comprehensive data format documentation for the CFCPN scraper outputs. Detail the JSON structure including scrapeTime metadata, total count, scraped count, and rows array containing procurement notice objects. Document each field definition: id (unique identifier), title (noticeTitle), publishTime, purchaser (userName), method (purchaseTypeLable), region (area), category (labelAllId), tags (yxCategoryNames), and source (noticeSource). Explain the CSV format with UTF-8 BOM encoding for Excel compatibility, including header row definitions and data escaping rules. Provide sample data structures showing the exact field mappings from the API response to the output format. Document data validation rules, null value handling, and character encoding considerations. Include examples of how to parse and process both JSON and CSV formats in different programming languages. Address data quality considerations and potential data cleaning requirements.","order":3,"progress_status":"completed","dependent_files":"scrape_cfcpn.js","gmt_create":"2026-07-03T17:40:09.142485+08:00","gmt_modified":"2026-07-03T17:41:20.2660864+08:00","raw_data":"WikiEncrypted:"},{"id":"701e7994-aa53-43fc-a9b5-afa96b0fae3b","repo_id":"c0c05551-5d15-47c1-b61f-b8c571f956c1","name":"API Reference","description":"api-reference","prompt":"Create API documentation for the CFCPN web scraping interface. Document the POST endpoint http://www.cfcpn.com/jcw/noticeinfo/noticeInfo/dataNoticeList including all request parameters: pageNo (page number), pageSize (fixed at 10), column (set to 'cggg'), searchType, searchContent, searchNoticeType, searchText, region, commonLabel1, commonLabel2, beginPublishTime, endPublishTime, searchVal, searchPurId, and labelAllId. Specify required headers including Content-Type application/x-www-form-urlencoded, User-Agent string, and Referer URL. Document the response schema with result boolean, total count, and rows array containing procurement notice objects. Include protocol-specific examples showing complete HTTP request/response cycles. Address rate limiting considerations with 500ms delays between requests. Document error responses and status codes. Provide client implementation guidelines for making direct API calls and handling authentication if required. Include debugging tools and monitoring approaches for API integration.","order":4,"progress_status":"completed","dependent_files":"scrape_cfcpn.js","gmt_create":"2026-07-03T17:40:09.142485+08:00","gmt_modified":"2026-07-03T17:41:41.1142235+08:00","raw_data":"WikiEncrypted:"},{"id":"667a2947-448c-41d3-9579-a100ff1a79c4","repo_id":"c0c05551-5d15-47c1-b61f-b8c571f956c1","name":"Development Guide","description":"development-guide","prompt":"Create development guide documentation for extending and maintaining the CFCPN scraper. Document the code structure with clear explanations of each function: fetchPage for HTTP communication, sleep for request throttling, csvEscape for data formatting, and main for orchestration. Explain the modular design patterns used despite being a single-file architecture. Provide extension points for adding new output formats, implementing retry logic, or integrating with databases. Document testing approaches using the existing test.py file structure. Include debugging techniques for network issues, API changes, and data parsing problems. Address performance optimization strategies for large-scale scraping operations. Document code style conventions and best practices for contributing to the project. Include deployment considerations for running the scraper in different environments (Windows, Linux, macOS). Provide migration guides for updating when the target API changes and backwards compatibility notes for maintaining older versions.","order":5,"progress_status":"completed","dependent_files":"scrape_cfcpn.js,test.py","gmt_create":"2026-07-03T17:40:09.142485+08:00","gmt_modified":"2026-07-03T17:41:40.7902474+08:00","raw_data":"WikiEncrypted:"}],"wiki_items":[{"catalog_id":"fbc6d1ac-f536-43a6-8d14-e7de80cca9e1","title":"Getting Started","description":"getting-started","extend":"{}","progress_status":"completed","repo_id":"c0c05551-5d15-47c1-b61f-b8c571f956c1","reference_count":0,"id":"697af6eb-28f4-4328-96ae-9d7fa8411dff","gmt_create":"2026-07-03T17:40:42.4645246+08:00","gmt_modified":"2026-07-03T17:40:42.4662151+08:00"},{"catalog_id":"a27ae80c-cee6-44e4-8468-57e1ef2e69c9","title":"Project Overview","description":"project-overview","extend":"{}","progress_status":"completed","repo_id":"c0c05551-5d15-47c1-b61f-b8c571f956c1","reference_count":0,"id":"afbfb1d0-7d35-40c3-bc25-bae222970e0b","gmt_create":"2026-07-03T17:40:43.6159129+08:00","gmt_modified":"2026-07-03T17:40:43.619463+08:00"},{"catalog_id":"747e2229-6e28-43d1-b74f-49cc511cad9a","title":"Core Features","description":"core-features","extend":"{}","progress_status":"completed","repo_id":"c0c05551-5d15-47c1-b61f-b8c571f956c1","reference_count":0,"id":"005c8f3c-529d-4389-a2bd-5adcfda0ee58","gmt_create":"2026-07-03T17:40:58.5042847+08:00","gmt_modified":"2026-07-03T17:40:58.5069219+08:00"},{"catalog_id":"4a460a2c-a6ae-40a0-9c52-ab826946bc32","title":"Data Formats","description":"data-formats","extend":"{}","progress_status":"completed","repo_id":"c0c05551-5d15-47c1-b61f-b8c571f956c1","reference_count":0,"id":"3c7c68c7-f088-4e81-b1e7-e0122cd16379","gmt_create":"2026-07-03T17:41:20.2623616+08:00","gmt_modified":"2026-07-03T17:41:20.266168+08:00"},{"catalog_id":"667a2947-448c-41d3-9579-a100ff1a79c4","title":"Development Guide","description":"development-guide","extend":"{}","progress_status":"completed","repo_id":"c0c05551-5d15-47c1-b61f-b8c571f956c1","reference_count":0,"id":"2536d739-a245-4f6f-918b-33a83060a9a0","gmt_create":"2026-07-03T17:41:40.786163+08:00","gmt_modified":"2026-07-03T17:41:40.7902474+08:00"},{"catalog_id":"701e7994-aa53-43fc-a9b5-afa96b0fae3b","title":"API Reference","description":"api-reference","extend":"{}","progress_status":"completed","repo_id":"c0c05551-5d15-47c1-b61f-b8c571f956c1","reference_count":0,"id":"2cf44192-c737-4457-869a-edfd7e30d484","gmt_create":"2026-07-03T17:41:41.1099788+08:00","gmt_modified":"2026-07-03T17:41:41.1142235+08:00"}],"wiki_overview":{"content":"\u003c/think\u003e\n\n\u003cblog\u003e\n\n# 金采网采购公告爬虫项目分析\n\n## 1. 项目介绍\n\n### 目的声明\n这是一个专门用于爬取中国政府采购网（CFCPN - China Financial Procurement Network）采购公告的Node.js脚本工具。该项目旨在自动化获取政府采购信息，为数据分析、市场研究或业务决策提供数据支持。\n\n### 核心目标和任务\n- **数据采集**：自动抓取金采网的采购公告信息\n- **数据处理**：将原始数据转换为结构化格式（JSON和CSV）\n- **用户友好**：提供命令行参数控制爬取范围和数量\n- **稳定性保障**：实现请求间隔和错误处理机制\n\n### 目标受众\n- 数据分析师和市场研究人员\n- 政府采购信息监控需求的企业\n- 需要批量获取采购数据的开发者\n\n## 2. 技术架构\n\n### 组件分解\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    A[主程序 main()] --\u003e B[API请求模块]\n    A --\u003e C[数据处理模块]\n    A --\u003e D[文件输出模块]\n    \n    B --\u003e E[HTTP客户端]\n    B --\u003e F[URL参数构建器]\n    B --\u003e G[响应解析器]\n    \n    C --\u003e H[数据映射器]\n    C --\u003e I[CSV转义器]\n    \n    D --\u003e J[JSON写入器]\n    D --\u003e K[CSV写入器]\n    \n    L[命令行参数] --\u003e A\n    M[配置常量] --\u003e A\n```\n\n### 设计模式\n- **模块化设计**：功能按职责分离，每个函数负责特定任务\n- **异步编程**：使用Promise和async/await处理网络请求\n- **错误处理**：统一的异常捕获和日志记录\n- **配置驱动**：通过命令行参数和常量配置行为\n\n### 系统关系\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant User as 用户\n    participant Script as 爬虫脚本\n    participant API as 金采网API\n    participant File as 文件系统\n    \n    User-\u003e\u003e+Script: 执行node scrape_cfcpn.js [页数]\n    Script-\u003e\u003e+API: POST /dataNoticeList (第1页)\n    API--\u003e\u003e-Script: 返回总条数和第一页数据\n    Script-\u003e\u003e+API: POST /dataNoticeList (第2-N页)\n    API--\u003e\u003e-Script: 返回分页数据\n    Script-\u003e\u003e+File: 写入JSON文件\n    Script-\u003e\u003e+File: 写入CSV文件\n    Script--\u003e\u003e-User: 显示爬取结果\n```\n\n### 数据流图\n```mermaid\nflowchart TD\n    A[命令行参数] --\u003e B[参数解析]\n    B --\u003e C[确定爬取范围]\n    C --\u003e D[API请求循环]\n    D --\u003e E[数据收集]\n    E --\u003e F[数据转换]\n    F --\u003e G[JSON格式化]\n    F --\u003e H[CSV格式化]\n    G --\u003e I[文件保存]\n    H --\u003e I\n    I --\u003e J[完成报告]\n```\n\n## 3. 关键实现\n\n### 主要入口点\n- **主脚本**: `scrape_cfcpn.js` - 爬虫的核心逻辑和流程控制\n\n### 核心模块\n- **API请求模块** (`fetchPage`函数): 处理与金采网API的HTTP通信\n- **数据处理模块** (`main`函数): 协调数据获取、处理和存储流程\n- **文件输出模块**: JSON和CSV格式的数据持久化\n\n### 配置方法\n- **API端点**: `http://www.cfcpn.com/jcw/noticeinfo/noticeInfo/dataNoticeList`\n- **页面大小**: 固定为10条记录每页\n- **输出文件**: \n  - `cfcpn_data.json` - 结构化JSON格式\n  - `cfcpn_data.csv` - CSV格式便于Excel打开\n\n### 外部依赖\n- **Node.js内置模块**:\n  - `http` - HTTP客户端\n  - `fs` - 文件系统操作\n  - `path` - 路径处理\n  - `URLSearchParams` - URL参数构建\n\n### 集成点\n- **金采网API**: 通过POST请求获取采购公告数据\n- **本地文件系统**: 输出处理后的数据文件\n\n### 组件关系图\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    A[命令行参数] --\u003e B[主控制器]\n    B --\u003e C[API客户端]\n    B --\u003e D[数据处理器]\n    B --\u003e E[文件写入器]\n    \n    C --\u003e F[HTTP请求]\n    C --\u003e G[JSON解析]\n    \n    D --\u003e H[字段映射]\n    D --\u003e I[CSV转义]\n    \n    E --\u003e J[JSON输出]\n    E --\u003e K[CSV输出]\n```\n\n## 4. 核心特性\n\n### 功能概览\n- **智能分页**: 自动检测总记录数并计算所需页数\n- **进度反馈**: 实时显示爬取进度和状态\n- **错误恢复**: 单个页面失败不影响整体爬取\n- **多格式输出**: 同时生成JSON和CSV两种格式\n- **防封禁机制**: 请求间隔控制避免被目标网站封禁\n\n### 实现亮点\n- **参数化控制**: 支持指定爬取页数或使用\"all\"参数\n- **数据清洗**: 自动过滤空值和特殊字符\n- **编码兼容**: CSV文件添加BOM头确保Excel正确显示中文\n- **内存优化**: 逐页处理避免一次性加载大量数据\n\n### 特性架构图\n```mermaid\nstateDiagram-v2\n    [*] --\u003e 初始化\n    初始化 --\u003e 获取总数: 请求第1页\n    获取总数 --\u003e 计算页数: 解析total字段\n    计算页数 --\u003e 开始爬取: 确定maxPages\n    开始爬取 --\u003e 请求页面: fetchPage()\n    请求页面 --\u003e 处理数据: 解析响应\n    处理数据 --\u003e 保存进度: 更新allRows数组\n    保存进度 --\u003e 请求页面: 下一页\n    请求页面 --\u003e 结束爬取: 达到maxPages\n    结束爬取 --\u003e 格式化数据: JSON/CSV转换\n    格式化数据 --\u003e 写入文件: 保存到磁盘\n    写入文件 --\u003e [*]: 完成\n```\n\n### 使用方法\n```bash\n# 默认爬取前5页（50条记录）\nnode scrape_cfcpn.js\n\n# 爬取前20页（200条记录）\nnode scrape_cfcpn.js 20\n\n# 爬取全部数据（注意：共14万+条，耗时较长）\nnode scrape_cfcpn.js all\n```\n\n## 5. 结论和建议\n\n### 项目架构总结\n该项目采用简洁高效的单文件架构，专注于单一任务（数据爬取），具有良好的代码组织和错误处理机制。使用Node.js原生模块避免了外部依赖，提高了部署便利性。\n\n### 架构优势\n- **简单直接**: 单文件结构易于理解和维护\n- **零依赖**: 仅使用Node.js内置模块\n- **健壮性**: 完善的错误处理和重试机制\n- **实用性**: 提供多种输出格式满足不同需求\n\n### 潜在改进领域\n- **并发控制**: 可考虑使用并发请求提高爬取效率\n- **断点续爬**: 实现已爬取页面的缓存机制\n- **配置管理**: 将硬编码参数移至配置文件\n- **日志系统**: 添加更详细的运行日志\n- **代理支持**: 增加代理服务器配置选项\n\n### 增强代码组织的可行建议\n1. **模块化重构**: 将不同功能拆分为独立模块\n2. **配置中心**: 创建独立的配置文件管理所有参数\n3. **错误分类**: 实现更细粒度的错误类型和处理策略\n4. **性能监控**: 添加爬取速度和成功率统计\n\n### 项目演进和维护的下一步\n1. **测试覆盖**: 为核心功能添加单元测试\n2. **文档完善**: 创建详细的使用说明和技术文档\n3. **版本管理**: 建立Git版本控制和发布流程\n4. **扩展性**: 设计插件架构支持其他数据源\n5. **监控告警**: 实现爬取失败的自动通知机制\n\nSources:\n- [scrape_cfcpn.js](scrape_cfcpn.js)\n- [test.py](test.py)\n\n\u003c/blog\u003e","gmt_create":"2026-07-03T17:39:17.2614592+08:00","gmt_modified":"2026-07-03T17:39:17.2614592+08:00","id":"5b9c04db-e608-45f6-b5ba-ea77ef188f6c","repo_id":"c0c05551-5d15-47c1-b61f-b8c571f956c1"},"wiki_readme":{"content":"No readme file","gmt_create":"2026-07-03T17:38:49.8156299+08:00","gmt_modified":"2026-07-03T17:38:49.8156299+08:00","id":"167bf83c-bacf-401f-a2ba-aeceda2d2230","repo_id":"c0c05551-5d15-47c1-b61f-b8c571f956c1"},"wiki_repo":{"id":"c0c05551-5d15-47c1-b61f-b8c571f956c1","name":"新建文件夹","progress_status":"completed","wiki_present_status":"COMPLETED","optimized_catalog":"\".\\n└── scrape_cfcpn.js\\n\"","current_document_structure":"WikiEncrypted:","catalogue_think_content":"WikiEncrypted:","recovery_checkpoint":"wiki_generation_completed","last_commit_id":"0000000000000000000000000000000000000000","last_commit_update":"2026-07-03T17:41:41.1178991+08:00","gmt_create":"2026-07-03T17:38:49.2134653+08:00","gmt_modified":"2026-07-03T17:41:41.1178991+08:00","extend_info":"{\"language\":\"en\",\"active\":true,\"branch\":\"Q0DeR-MaG1C-BrAnCh-Fo2-NoN-GiT-Or-No-C0MmIt\",\"shareStatus\":\"\",\"server_error_code\":\"\",\"cosy_version\":\"\"}"}}